<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 11:41PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Armstrong and southeastern Randall Counties through 1245 AM CDT...
At 1141 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Happy, or 15 miles north of Tulia, moving east at 25
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wayside.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
